00:01:33,586 --> 00:01:37,369
[SPEAKER_05]: Thank you so much, President Morrell, and thank you so much to the city staff who are here tonight.

29
00:01:37,509 --> 00:01:53,441
[SPEAKER_05]: And I know all these folks were present at our previous housing subcommittee meeting before this was passed to Committee of the Whole and provided some really excellent feedback and voices of support for this ordinance and context around, you know, what this aims to do in the community.

30
00:01:53,481 --> 00:01:57,705
[SPEAKER_05]: So I really appreciate your time and being here tonight, as well as your past feedback.

31
00:01:59,326 --> 00:02:07,811
[SPEAKER_05]: So, this draft housing stability notification ordinance for fellow counselors who are not on the housing subcommittee and are less familiar with it.

32
00:02:08,411 --> 00:02:13,694
[SPEAKER_05]: This ordinance is very similar to an ordinance that is already on the books and several of our neighboring communities.

33
00:02:14,294 --> 00:02:16,035
[SPEAKER_05]: Cambridge, Somerville, and Boston.

34
00:02:16,555 --> 00:02:18,476
[SPEAKER_05]: The ordinance is very straightforward.

35
00:02:19,857 --> 00:02:35,824
[SPEAKER_05]: What it does is it creates a requirement that any property owner in Medford where they have a tenant at the beginning of that tenancy, they are to send to their tenant a document that the city of Medford

36
00:02:36,604 --> 00:02:48,520
[SPEAKER_05]: will create that outlines basic housing rights and resources and also points occupants to where they can find out more about their housing rights and resources and organizations to provide more information about that.

37
00:02:49,384 --> 00:03:09,032
[SPEAKER_05]: And also at the termination of a lease or if a homeowner is foreclosed upon for that same document to be sent to them and the goal of this is to promote housing stability in Medford by making sure that people know at regular times or being being able to catch people at certain moments when they're moving into a new place or moving out of it.

38
00:03:09,712 --> 00:03:25,617
[SPEAKER_05]: So that everybody has the information that they should who to go to if you need help navigating a housing issue of any type, what type of resources are out there and how to get in contact with them with the goal of providing you know knowledge is power and we make sure that people are receiving

39
00:03:26,145 --> 00:03:37,688
[SPEAKER_05]: this information through now structured channels that everybody benefits, tenants benefit, homeowners moving out of their homes benefit, and also landlords span to benefit by everybody being on the same page.

40
00:03:38,669 --> 00:03:41,849
[SPEAKER_05]: So we've discussed this a couple times in the housing subcommittee.

41
00:03:42,950 --> 00:03:51,352
[SPEAKER_05]: To recap our last meeting, we got more feedback from city staff from planning development and sustainability and prevention and outreach.

42
00:03:52,152 --> 00:03:52,332
[SPEAKER_05]: And

