124
00:11:21,509 --> 00:11:21,749
[SPEAKER_05]: So,

125
00:11:24,535 --> 00:11:25,676
[SPEAKER_05]: Chapter 49, housing.

126
00:11:26,777 --> 00:11:42,891
[SPEAKER_05]: We have the stated purpose of this ordinance to promote the housing stability of Medford residents, and then we have a fairly lengthy section on definitions, which seeks to just make sure that we're on the same page with some of the terms that we are using when we use this ordinance, which is pretty straightforward.

127
00:11:43,631 --> 00:11:46,013
[SPEAKER_05]: The definitions make up about a third of the overall ordinance.

128
00:11:48,015 --> 00:11:52,479
[SPEAKER_05]: Entity for homeowner, foreclosing owner, essentially the parties involved in the

129
00:11:53,316 --> 00:11:56,619
[SPEAKER_05]: landlord-occupant relationship and the places that they reside in.

130
00:11:59,681 --> 00:12:04,946
[SPEAKER_07]: We get to applicability, it speaks to who is involved.

131
00:12:08,078 --> 00:12:14,180
[SPEAKER_05]: And this makes clear that we are talking about specifically residential spaces.

132
00:12:14,780 --> 00:12:22,762
[SPEAKER_05]: This section also makes clear that this ordinance does not apply to rental units in health care facilities.

133
00:12:22,782 --> 00:12:30,985
[SPEAKER_05]: This is applying to houses, this is applying to apartments, living situations, not boarding or medical situations.

134
00:12:33,730 --> 00:12:36,731
[SPEAKER_05]: 4934 is the meat of the ordinance talking about the required notices.

135
00:12:36,771 --> 00:12:39,752
[SPEAKER_05]: This is the thrust of the ordinance, and we have two sections here.

136
00:12:39,772 --> 00:12:45,674
[SPEAKER_05]: We're sorry, we have four sections here, but the first two are talking about inception and termination.

137
00:12:46,774 --> 00:12:49,455
[SPEAKER_05]: There is a notice issued at the inception of a tenancy.

138
00:12:51,316 --> 00:12:59,581
[SPEAKER_05]: whenever a landlord enters into a new tenancy with a tenant under written lease, written tenancy at will, or oral tenancy at will, regardless of length.

139
00:12:59,601 --> 00:13:11,168
[SPEAKER_05]: So that's saying regardless of the formality of the rental agreement, this ordinance still applies, and that housing rights and resources notice must still be issued to the tenant.

140
00:13:14,190 --> 00:13:18,413
[SPEAKER_05]: It describes how the notice will be conveyed, in hand or by certified mail,

141
00:13:19,328 --> 00:13:21,349
[SPEAKER_05]: in addition to by email if one is available.

142
00:13:23,389 --> 00:13:32,572
[SPEAKER_05]: And this notice shall include translated instructions for how to readily access the included information and resources in languages other than English.

143
00:13:32,912 --> 00:13:40,775
[SPEAKER_05]: That last part is something that we had a very rich discussion with the city staff at our last subcommittee meeting, how to handle the translation piece.

144
00:13:40,795 --> 00:13:45,116
[SPEAKER_05]: This is something that some of our neighboring communities with this ordinance have done differently.

145
00:13:45,776 --> 00:13:50,060
[SPEAKER_05]: Some of them include more translated text on the document itself.

146
00:13:50,620 --> 00:13:56,345
[SPEAKER_05]: Some of them simply have a more simpler streamlined version, which is a translation of the sentence.

147
00:13:57,065 --> 00:14:02,590
[SPEAKER_05]: This notice is important, please have it translated in major languages spoken in that community.

148
00:14:03,831 --> 00:14:11,838
[SPEAKER_05]: So this we did finesse with the input of city staff for how to strike the right balance of managing city capacity and our limited translation resources with

149
00:14:12,458 --> 00:14:21,464
[SPEAKER_05]: making sure that regardless of language spoken at home, this form would be readable and meaningful to everybody who receives it.

150
00:14:22,324 --> 00:14:25,286
[SPEAKER_05]: And then termination of tenancy is extremely similar.

151
00:14:25,547 --> 00:14:33,932
[SPEAKER_05]: It stipulates the same notice be sent just when the tenant or former homeowners is served a notice to quit or lease non-renewal or expiration.

152
00:14:37,703 --> 00:14:43,346
[SPEAKER_05]: Later in this section, we have a couple amendments that were adopted from our last subcommittee meeting.

153
00:14:44,427 --> 00:14:49,950
[SPEAKER_05]: We wanted to make sure that there was, you know, a structure for input on how to make sure

154
00:14:51,131 --> 00:14:57,534
[SPEAKER_05]: that we are thinking about diversity, we're thinking about equity, we're thinking about how this will land with residents of different backgrounds.

155
00:14:58,535 --> 00:15:11,081
[SPEAKER_05]: When this form is created, so we included Section C, the Board of Health Director or their designee shall consult the Office of Diversity, Equity, Inclusion and Office of Planning, Development, Sustainability and the Office of Prevention and Outreach on the creation of the required notices.

156
00:15:14,144 --> 00:15:29,070
[SPEAKER_05]: And finally, that there'll be a procedure for making sure on an annual basis that the notices are still relevant include all the information that they should just to go quickly through the remainder non wavability, this is to say you can't make a rental lease and landlord that says this ordinance doesn't apply that always applies.

157
00:15:31,930 --> 00:15:33,952
[SPEAKER_05]: And finally, enforcement.

158
00:15:34,532 --> 00:15:43,358
[SPEAKER_05]: Initially, in the first draft of this ordinance, we use the model of other communities, which said, which in other communities, this is typically enforced by the code enforcement officer.

159
00:15:44,279 --> 00:15:47,121
[SPEAKER_05]: Through the subcommittee process, we reached out to the code enforcement officer.

160
00:15:47,701 --> 00:15:49,963
[SPEAKER_05]: They said, this sounds like more of a Board of Health thing.

161
00:15:50,003 --> 00:15:58,569
[SPEAKER_05]: We reached out to the Board of Health and Director O'Connor very graciously agreed that her office would be able to handle it and would be happy to handle enforcement.

162
00:15:58,649 --> 00:15:59,210
[SPEAKER_05]: Thank you very much.

163
00:15:59,810 --> 00:16:02,033
[SPEAKER_05]: And so that was one change that was made in subcommittee.

164
00:16:03,014 --> 00:16:16,108
[SPEAKER_05]: And then this section also includes that the penalty, which he was I think very closely to other penalties levied for other ordinances in Medford, such as the snow removal ordinance with that maximum fine of $300.

165
